article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 82, Texas State 62
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Antuane Miller came off the bench to score 23 points in Stephen F. Austin's 82-62 victory over Texas State on Thursday night. Miller was 10-of-11 from the field and 3-of-4 from the free throw line. Matt Kingsley added 14 points while Josh Alexander and Will Johnson each had nine points. The Lumberjacks (12-6, 5-1 Southland) held the Bobcats to just two field goals in the final 10 minutes of the first half and led 42-24 at halftime. They built a 27-point lead with 4:26 remaining in the game. The Bobcats (8-12, 3-4) struggled on offense, hitting only 37 percent of their shots compared to 65 percent shooting by Stephen F. Austin. Brandon Bush led Texas State with 19 points and six rebounds. Chris Agwumaro added 11 points and five rebounds.
